Environment: Next.js 15 App Router at clock.meavo.app (Vercel, fra1). NOT the legacy Express app in `api/` or the Vite SPA in `web/` вЂ” those are superseded reference code.

## Stack

- Next.js 15 App Router, TypeScript strict (`allowJs` for legacy `.jsx` components), React 19, Tailwind CSS 3
- Prisma 6 via `@meavo/db` git tag в†’ shared Neon Postgres (`Clock*` models, `clock_*` tables)
- NextAuth v5 JWT, Google invite-only (`@meavo.com`), `ToolCardAccess` gate on `seed-clock-tool`
- ESP32 kiosk firmware (PlatformIO C++) in `firmware/` talks to `/api/device/*` with `X-Device-Key`

## Do NOT

- Edit the Prisma schema here вЂ” schema lives in meavo-db; bump the git tag in `package.json`
- Run `prisma db push` from this repo вЂ” shared DB; script is intentionally disabled
- Add features to `api/` or `web/` вЂ” legacy trees, read-only reference
- Add shadcn/Radix/MUI вЂ” use utility classes from `src/app/globals.css` (`btn-primary`, `card`, `input`, `page-title`)
- Skip `requireAdminApi()` (admin routes) or `assertDeviceAuth()` (device routes) вЂ” middleware passes `/api/*` through
- Look up the tool card by `linkedAppKey` вЂ” use `CLOCK_TOOL_CARD_ID` from `src/lib/constants.ts`
- Change `tappedAt` from string site-local time to `DateTime` вЂ” stats math and firmware depend on it
- Commit secrets, `.env.local`, or `firmware/include/config.h`

## Code layout

| Area | Path |
|------|------|
| Admin pages (thin wrappers) | `src/app/(app)/*/page.tsx` |
| Page implementations (client) | `src/components/clock-pages/*.jsx` |
| Admin REST API | `src/app/api/*` (workers, pending_uids, card_bindings, clock_events, stats) |
| Kiosk device API | `src/app/api/device/*` |
| Domain logic | `src/lib/clock/` (events, pending, stats, workers, serialize) |
| Auth | `src/middleware.ts`, `src/lib/auth.ts`, `src/lib/meavo-auth.ts`, `src/lib/admin-api.ts`, `src/lib/device-auth.ts` |
| Firmware | `firmware/src/main.cpp`, `firmware/include/` |
| Legacy (read-only) | `api/` (Express + SQLite), `web/` (Vite SPA) |

## Data flow

```
ESP32 kiosk в”Ђв”ЂX-Device-Keyв”Ђв”Ђв–¶ /api/device/clock_event в”Ђв–¶ src/lib/clock/events.ts в”Ђв–¶ Neon (clock_events)
                              /api/device/pending_uid в”Ђв–¶ src/lib/clock/pending.ts в”Ђв–¶ (clock_pending_uids)
Admin browser в”Ђв”Ђsessionв”Ђв”Ђв–¶ /(app) pages в”Ђв–¶ src/lib/api.ts (usePoll) в”Ђв–¶ /api/* в”Ђв–¶ src/lib/clock/* в”Ђв–¶ Neon
Gateway (meavo.app) в”Ђв–¶ grants ToolCardAccess (seed-clock-tool) в”Ђв–¶ login + every request re-checked
```

Unknown card taps become pending UIDs (15-min TTL); admins assign them to workers on `/pending`, expiry is handled lazily in `src/lib/clock/pending.ts` and by `GET /api/cron/expire-pending`.

